result.execSummary:
The defendant Cassandra M. Wildman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Cassandra M. Wildman in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Defendant Cassandra M. Wildman in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF192, 15CF156 and 18CF34 @ 2:50 p.m. Agreement stated - 18CF34 Def will plead to charge, 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 mo ic, 24 mo es, concurrent to any other serving. 15CF156 ct 1 - 48 mo prison, 24 mo ic, 24 mo es, concurrent to any, 304 cays credit. 14CF192 ct 1 - 48 mo prison, 24 mo ic, 24 mo es, concurrent to any other currently serving. 304 days credit. Def eligible for SAP and CIP. Costs on 18CF34. Atty Laufenberg agrees. 18CF34 information being filed, mirrors complaint. Off the record briefly. Def understands agreement and agrees with terms. Court reviews prelim rights w/Def. Court accepts waiver as knowing and voluntary, finds probable cause and binds over in 18CF34. Copy of information received, reading waived, reserve objections. Parties have received revocation summary. No additions or corrections. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to 18CF34 ct 1 - no contest. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands and plea freely and voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds Def guilty of 18CF34 ct 1. Sentencing remarks by State. Sentencing remarks by Atty Laufenberg. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will follow agreement. Orders on 18CF34 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 months ic, 24 months es, costs, DNA surcharge. 15CF156 ct 1, 4 yrs prison, 2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, credit for 304 days served. Outstanding costs to be paid through es on both cases. 14CF192 4 yrs prison, 2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, credit for 304 days served. Def is eligible for SAP and CIP. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. Postconviction rights. 18CF34 - DNA sample if not already on file.
